title: Bao Bao the panda heads home to China
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device Bao Bao the panda heads home to China 21 February 2017 Last updated at 22:43 GMT 
Bao Bao, a three-year-old panda who has captured the hearts of Americans since her birth at the National Zoo in Washington, has departed for China. 
He will join the Chinese panda breeding programme after first completing a 16-hour flight. 
Hopefully he won't face any excess baggage costs - he has about 55lbs (25kg) of bamboo with him, as well as a few other snacks. 
The BBC's Laura Trevelyan reports.
